translated:
Ögren, Carl Olof, acting chief physician, Jönköping, born on June 23, 1901 in Blidsberg, Älvsborg County, son of Carl Ö. and Ida Stenlund. Married in 1936 to Karin Gustafson. Children: Eva Karin, born in 1938, Anna Brita, born in 1942, Sven Olof, born in 1945. 

Education: Passed student examination in Borås in 1920, graduated from Gothenburg's Handelsinstitut, medical bachelor's degree in 1927, and medical license in Stockholm in 1933. 

Professional experience: Assistant physician at Sahlgren's Hospital medical department in 1933, assistant physician at Ulricehamns sanatorium in 1933-1934, physician at Djursätra spa in 1936, at Skagersbrunn in 1936 and 1937, extra assistant physician and substitute assistant at Psychiatric Hospital in 1935-1937, assistant physician there in 1937-1938, acting secondary physician there in 1938, assistant physician at Seraf Hospital's neurology clinic, secondary physician at Ryhov Hospital in Jönköping since 1939, acting chief physician of the psychiatric ward at Jönköping prison in 1946-1947, acting chief physician there. Psychiatric advisor to the board for the State Vocational School Långanäs since 1943, at Jönköping public school since 1943, and at Jönköping Child Welfare Board since 1944.
